# CHECKSUMS.sha256 — Peership Corpus v1.0.0
#
# Every frozen artifact in this repository, with its SHA-256 digest, the exact
# filename it carries in its Zenodo deposit, and the record it came from.
#
# WHY THIS FILE EXISTS
# PROVENANCE.md claims the committed artifacts are byte-identical copies of the
# archived deposits. This file is what lets a stranger TEST that claim instead of
# trusting it. It also lets an auditor match files across the one rename this
# repository made (the ISONOMIA preprint, see VERSION_MANIFEST.md D2), where the
# repository filename and the Zenodo filename deliberately differ.
#
# HOW TO VERIFY
#   sha256sum -c CHECKSUMS.sha256
# and, to check against the archive rather than against this file, download each
# record's files from the DOI below and compare digests.
#
# VERIFIED 2026-07-14. Papers I-IV were checked against live downloads from their
# Zenodo records. The thesis, the companion, and the three apparatus files were
# checked against the deposit's own MANIFEST_sha256.txt AND against the copies
# inside Peership_v1.0_complete_release.zip. All matched.
#
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# repository path                                    <- Zenodo filename @ record
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
